{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"walkableRadius"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int32","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int32V"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The parameter "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder\/Config\/walkableRadius"},{"type":"text","text":" defines the worldspace agent radius "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"r"},{"type":"text","text":" in voxels."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Most often, this value of #walkableRadius should be calculated as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ceil(r \/ cs)"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note this is based on #cs since the agent radius is always parallel to the ground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"plane."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder\/Config\/walkableRadius"},{"type":"text","text":" value is greater than zero, the edges of the navmesh will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be pushed away from all obstacles by this amount."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A non-zero "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder\/Config\/walkableRadius"},{"type":"text","text":" allows for much simpler runtime navmesh collision checks."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The game only needs to check that the center point of the agent is contained within"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a navmesh polygon.  Without this erosion, runtime navigation checks need to collide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the geometric projection of the agentâ€™s logical cylinder onto the navmesh with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"boundary edges of the navmesh polygons."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In general, this is the closest any part of the final mesh should get to an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"obstruction in the source geometry.  It is usually set to the maximum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"agent radius."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to have tight-fitting navmesh, or want to reuse the same navmesh for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"multiple agents with differing radii, you can use a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder\/Config\/walkableRadius"},{"type":"text","text":" value of zero."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Be advised though that you will need to perform your own collisions with the navmesh"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"edges, and odd edge cases issues in the mesh generation can potentially occur.  For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these reasons, specifying a radius of zero is allowed but is not recommended."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftnavigation\/navmeshbuilder\/config\/walkableradius"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder\/Config\/walkableRadius","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The distance to erode\/shrink the walkable area of the heightfield away from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"obstructions.  [Limit: >=0] [Units: vx]"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"walkableRadius"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int32","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int32V"}],"title":"walkableRadius","roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","externalID":"s:15SwiftNavigation14NavMeshBuilderC6ConfigV14walkableRadiuss5Int32Vvp","modules":[{"name":"SwiftNavigation"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation","doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder","doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder\/Config"]]},"references":{"doc://SwiftNavigation/documentation/SwiftNavigation":{"role":"collection","title":"SwiftNavigation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create and use navigation meshes in your Swift and RealityKit applications."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftnavigation"},"doc://SwiftNavigation/documentation/SwiftNavigation/NavMeshBuilder/Config":{"role":"symbol","title":"NavMeshBuilder.Config","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Config"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The configuration parameters that drive the creation of your navigation mesh."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder\/Config","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Config"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftnavigation\/navmeshbuilder\/config"},"doc://SwiftNavigation/documentation/SwiftNavigation/NavMeshBuilder":{"role":"symbol","title":"NavMeshBuilder","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NavMeshBuilder"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a navigational mesh based on your geometry."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"NavMeshBuilder"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftnavigation\/navmeshbuilder"},"doc://SwiftNavigation/documentation/SwiftNavigation/NavMeshBuilder/Config/walkableRadius":{"role":"symbol","title":"walkableRadius","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"walkableRadius"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int32","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int32V"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The distance to erode\/shrink the walkable area of the heightfield away from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"obstructions.  [Limit: >=0] [Units: vx]"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftNavigation\/documentation\/SwiftNavigation\/NavMeshBuilder\/Config\/walkableRadius","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftnavigation\/navmeshbuilder\/config\/walkableradius"}}}